genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica duranguense
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica duranguense is a regional Mexican music genre that originated in the state of Durango. It is characterized by its use of wind and brass instruments, such as the tambora and clarinet, and its upbeat tempo and danceable rhythms. The lyrics often focus on themes of love and heartbreak, as well as regional pride and identity.
